dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq b DJ Bravo 75 (112b 3x4 2x6 128m) SR: 66.96

dismissalComment.html: he charges down too early and Bravo delivers a good yorker on the middle stump from round the wicket! Misbah is late to bring his bat down in time and sees his stumps splayed!

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal not out 40 (31b 6x4 0x6 40m) SR: 129.03

dismissalComment.html: Has this been taken? Roach does that trick at the fine-leg boundary - he takes the catch, realises his falling over, pops it back in, goes out and comes back to complete the catch. But there is a problem, his left foot was too close the rope and the umpires are looking at it. But they are happy with it, Shehzad has to go. He top-edged his pull shot high and for a moment it looked like it was going to sail over the fielder. Good catch by Roach

commentTextItems.html: and it's a tie would you believe it! Wahab aims to pitch it fuller on the stumps and doesn't quite succeed, Holder swings and he gets a thick edge that goes past the keeper and races to third man, the throw from Junaid was to the keeper Akmal who didn't collect it at all, not sure what went wrong with Akmal because it wasn't exactly the worst throw

commentPostTextItems.html: Misbah: "The way Holder played he took the game away. In the last over we bowled too many full deliveries. I thought 229 was a fightable total, but in the end we missed a couple of tricks. There were a lot of dot balls (in our innings), I thought we were 30 runs short."

Bravo: "I'm also disappointed, this was a game we were supposed to win. It should never have reached that situation, leaving it to the lower order, given the number of batsmen we have. At this level, the number of dot balls in our innings was unacceptable. We need to come up with a plan to cut down on that, back to the drawing board. All in all I was happy with our bowling, we kept them to 229, we had to expect that knock from Akmal. Sunil and Jason had no choice but to go for their shots."
Misbah and Lendl Simmons will share the Man of the Match award.
Misbah: "The ball was gripping, not coming onto the bat."
Simmons: "Thought it was a good batting wicket. Didn't get many big scores in the last two games. We wanted to rotate the strike. Good performance from Sunil and Jason."

That's it from us here. I suppose many of you are still in shock. Those in Pakistan and this corner of the world may not sleep for a while! It's 3AM as I write. Thanks for your company. We'll see you again for the 4th ODI on Sunday. Cheers!

End of match: Jailbreak for West Indies! Pakistan are shell shocked to say the least because this was their game to lose before the last over commenced. With 15 to defend, you will always back yourself. If there's one person you shouldn't be standing next to right now, it's Whatmore. He was fuming after Wahab conceded that six. West Indies feel like they have won this. Pakistan are dejected. You have to feel for them.
Quite a few have commented on that short run during the Pakistan innings.
Uzair: "That one run short called incorrectly by the umpire is the difference here."
Cheema: "Now who is going to correct that mistake by the umpire who called it a short run when it wasn't when Akmal and Riaz were batting in the first inning."
Mazher Arshad has this eerie stat: "This is Pakistan's second tied match in the last two months. Margin to defend in last over was same in both -15!"
Rameez Raja says he would have given the last over to Hafeez instead of Wahab.

commentTextItems.html: hang on! Holder knocks off 6 of those! Wahab bowling length, Holder makes room and carves that clean over extra cover, seriously that was not a fluke hit from a No.11, it was a genuine shot

commentPostTextItems.html: Dav Whatmore was fuming, plenty of fielders gather around Wahab

commentTextItems.html: some respite for Wahab as he shortens the length down the leg side and Holder swings and misses

oh well six off the over already! Wahab goes over the wicket and pitches it up, Holder makes room and drives crisply wide of cover, for some reason the boundaries are not as protected as they should be
that was quite a clean strike by Roach but Misbah was alert at cover to cut that off

commentPostTextItems.html: WI FAN: "Would be a miracle if Holder or Roach pulled a Dhoni!"

commentTextItems.html: close call for Pakistan first up as Holder gets on outside edge past the keeper, third man is more fine so he could cut that off
Junaid responds well with a yorker fired outside off, too quick for Roach to get his bat down and make something of it

commentPostTextItems.html: Mohsin Zunzunia: "Wow! Never seem Pakistan field so great collectively!"

stays back and clips it down to short fine leg

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c Roach b Holder 17 (44b 2x4 0x6 48m) SR: 38.63

dismissalComment.html: Has this been taken? Roach does that trick at the fine-leg boundary - he takes the catch, realises his falling over, pops it back in, goes out and comes back to complete the catch. But there is a problem, his left foot was too close the rope and the umpires are looking at it. But they are happy with it, Shehzad has to go. He top-edged his pull shot high and for a moment it looked like it was going to sail over the fielder. Good catch by Roach

image.caption: Kemar Roach player portrait
image.longCaption: Kemar Roach player portrait, West Indies media day

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Jamshed c Roach b Sammy 20 (28b 2x4 0x6 51m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: another top-edge! another wicket! Sammy gets a wicket and the smallish crowd can be heard now. Jamshed makes mess of a decent start, he tried to pull this short of length delivery from outside off. It got a touch big on him and the top-edge settled into the hands of Roach at mid-on

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Sammy b DJ Bravo 14 (33b 0x4 0x6 63m) SR: 42.42

dismissalComment.html: soft dismissal! Bravo continues with the short stuff to Hafeez, he can't resist going for the pull, gets a top edge and Sammy takes the easiest of catches at square leg, Hafeez beaten for a bit of pace too

image.caption: Kemar Roach player portrait
image.longCaption: Kemar Roach player portrait, West Indies media day

headshotImage.caption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Haris Sohail c Pollard b Roach 26 (37b 2x4 0x6 51m) SR: 70.27

dismissalComment.html: this wicket has come from nowhere! Sohail gets a short and wide dolly and he crashes it off the back foot again, but it's in the air and it's straight to Pollard at point, he gobbles it up

headshotImage.caption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dwayne Bravo player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq b DJ Bravo 75 (112b 3x4 2x6 128m) SR: 66.96

dismissalComment.html: he charges down too early and Bravo delivers a good yorker on the middle stump from round the wicket! Misbah is late to bring his bat down in time and sees his stumps splayed!

headshotImage.caption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sunil Narine player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi c Narine b Holder 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: well, almost everyone is top-edging and so does Boom Boom! Short ball, he goes for a pull, gets a thick top edge that flies to Narine at fine leg

headshotImage.caption: Junaid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Junaid Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle b Junaid Khan 8 (12b 1x4 0x6 20m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: dragged it on! Gayle's horror form continues, Junaid gave him a bit of width and Gayle's foot movement was as good as nothing, half-heartedly poked his bat out and the inside edge hit the off stump

dismissalText.long: c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Irfan
dismissalText.commentary: Johnson Charles c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Irfan 6 (6b 1x4 0x6 12m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: thick edge! Irfan bowled that on a good length outside off, straightened a bit and Charles was half forward and poked his bat at it, Akmal takes the edge

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Hafeez b Wahab Riaz
dismissalText.commentary: Darren Bravo c Mohammad Hafeez b Wahab Riaz 17 (40b 2x4 0x6 65m) SR: 42.5

dismissalComment.html: this is the end of Lil Bravo!Another short delivery strikes gold today. Lil Bravo tried to nudge it to the leg side, but it was well directed and it kept rising on to him, the batsman was hit on the shoulder of the bat and it just lobbed up on the leg side. The fielder from square leg runs in and takes a good catch diving forward. It's the Prof there, he makes himself useful. Lil Bravo falls in his teens

dismissalText.long: c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Irfan
dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels c Umar Akmal b Mohammad Irfan 46 (106b 4x4 0x6 140m) SR: 43.39

dismissalComment.html: Samuels' struggle ends, Irfan replaces Wahab and strikes immediately, pitches it on middle and leg and Samuels makes room and slash that over the off side, gets a thick edge to Akmal, more in desperation than anything else

headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Ahmed Shehzad b Saeed Ajmal
dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c Ahmed Shehzad b Saeed Ajmal 75 (86b 7x4 2x6 120m) SR: 87.2

dismissalComment.html: brilliantly taken by Shehzad! Ajmal drops it fractionally short and Simmons goes for the pull, Shehzad ran to his left from deep midwicket, covered a lot of ground and timed his jump well, just managed to hang on and he hurt himself after taking the catch
